Level 3: Hard
Q36. What is the output and why?
class A:
    x = []
a1 = A()
a2 = A()
a1.x.append(1)
print(a2.x)
A: [1] — x is a mutable class variable shared by all instances. Classic interview trap. Prefer setting mutable data in __init__ as instance attributes.
