Q37. What is the output?
class Student:
    school = "ABC"
    def __init__(self, name):
        self.name = name
s1 = Student("Sai")
s1.school = "ZP"
print(Student.school)
print(s1.__dict__)
print(Student.__dict__["school"])
A:
ABC
{'name': 'Sai', 'school': 'ZP'}
ABC
s1.school = "ZP" creates an instance attribute; class attribute stays "ABC".
