Q42. What is the output?
class A:
    def show(self):
        print("A")
class B(A):
    def show(self):
        print("B")
obj = B()
A.show(obj)
obj.show()
A:
A
B
You can call the parent method explicitly with the instance; normal call uses the overridden method.
