Q44. What is the MRO and why does it matter for classes/objects?
A: Method Resolution Order — the lookup path Python uses when calling a method on an object with inheritance (especially multiple inheritance). Inspect with ClassName.__mro__ or ClassName.mro().
print(Child.__mro__)
________________________________________
Q45. What is the output?
class Data:
    def __init__(self, nums):
        self.nums = nums
d1 = Data([1, 2])
d2 = d1
d3 = copy.copy(d1)
d1.nums.append(3)
print(d2.nums)
print(d3.nums)
A:
[1, 2, 3]
[1, 2, 3]
Assignment and shallow copy both share the inner list. Only deepcopy would isolate nested mutables.
