Q46. Why can print(acc.__balance) fail but print(acc.__dict__) still show private data?
A: Attribute access uses name mangling / lookup rules. The real storage is still in the instance __dict__ under the mangled name _BankAccount__balance. Encapsulation in Python is by convention, not hard enforcement.
