Q47. What is the difference between class object and instance object in memory terms?
A:
•	Class object — one object representing the class (Student), holds class attributes/methods
•	Instance objects — many objects created from that class, each with its own __dict__ for instance data
Attribute lookup: instance → class → bases (MRO).
